{
  "texts": [
    "After successfully training the reward model, annotators can distinguish the quality of AI outputs and effectively reward behaviors that meet expectations.",
    "However, training the reward model alone is insufficient for continuous optimization of AI behavior.",
    "The next step is to apply these rewards in a dynamic learning process to further adjust and optimize the AI's behavior strategy.",
    "This brings us to Step 4: using Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) reinforcement learning algorithms to optimize AI behavior based on feedback from the reward model.",
    "The PPO algorithm helps adjust and refine AI behavior strategies so that future actions achieve higher rewards (Schulman et al., 2017)."
  ]
}